// inside root
// all dirs require root permission except home
bin: binary files, programs for machine
boot: files the kernel needs to boot, system folder
cdrom: cds used to mount here, now legacy
dev: devices, all devices connected
etc: configuration files for system
home: all user files
lib and lib64: library files for programs to use
media: usb drives will show up in media (shows up on desktop of ubuntu)
opt: optional, where some programs are stored (like google chrome on ubuntu)
tmp: temperary, where temp files live (usually cleared on startup)
var: variable data, like logs and caches and backups etc
sbin: more binaries usually used by the system
root: root users home directory
usr: universal system resources, like desktop pics, able to use by multiple users



